<p class="EnTeteTranscription">Thomson, John. Journal, Mackenzie River, 1800-1802. An electronic transcription. MFTP #0021</p><div class="ContenuPage">
<p style="text-align:justify;">Thursday the 16<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Considerable quantity of Drift Ice<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The Men hard at work making the hangard, gave each of the women 4 Sinews to make Hare snares &amp; sent 8 to the little Chiefs women for the same purpose<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Friday the 17<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  All hands at work the same as yesterday<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Saturday the 18<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  In the evening finished the Hangard, got all the property carried into it, everything is at present dieu merci safe under Lock &amp; key &#8211; gave the Men a Dram<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The Little blind Chief &amp; his Son came to pay me a vissit, the former in expectation that I would restore him his sight<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> gave him a Dram &amp; p<sup>s</sup> of Tobacco<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Sunday the 19<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Early this morning the Men fell to work about the house.  Raised the Entourage to the Windows<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The Little Chiefs young Son &amp; Brother in law brought a Green orignal skin &amp; 18 hares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Monday the 20<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent off the 2 young Men to set Snares, gave them 110 for that purpose<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Sent the women to cut hay for the chimnies, they brought enough for one<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The Men finished the Entourage of the house &amp; cut a few pieces for the covering<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Tuesday the 21<sup>st</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Squarred &amp; put up all the Covering of the House, the size of the Entourage is 32 feet long, 17 wide, &amp; 7½ High, &amp; is considering the shortness of time about it very well made<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Very Cold<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Wednesday the 22<sup>d</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Commenced making the 2 chimnies<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> made about one half<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> gave the Men a Dram<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The hunters brought 13 hares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Thursday the 23<sup>d</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Finished the Chimnies &amp; put up the Gable ends of the House, the hunters brought only 8 hares<span class="AddHand-editors">[,]</span> one of them went away<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Friday the 24<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Three Men plaistered the Roof &amp; the 2 others squared about the one half of the Floor.  Sent the Little Chiefs Son to vissit the Snares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Prie of Hares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">Saturday the 25<sup>th</sup><span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The y Man brought 30 hares<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Covered the Roof with Earth, plaistered all the outside of the house</p>
<p style="text-align:right;">&amp;</p>

